    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-04T03:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-04T03:10:00-05:00" n="944"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d944">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00/3–446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-04T04:10:00-04:00"
                            >March 4, 1946—4:10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:29 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. President confirmed to me this morning plan to hold elections for Congress
                    this year. I expressed hope Liberal Party as such would not be barred from
                    elections. He said status of Liberal Party would be decided by the courts.</p>
                <p>He again expressed hope we would help to reorganize Paraguayan police as
                    necessary aid to development of democratic institutions in Paraguay. I said it
                    would not be possible for us to do anything at this stage but that we might be
                    helpful after positive steps toward democratization had been taken.</p>
                <p>President expressed gratitude for extension of Stica<note n="3" xml:id="d944fn3"
                        >Servicio Técnieo Interamericano de Cooperación Agrícola, an agriculture
                        development company.</note> agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
